           SPELL=foomatic-db-hpijs
         VERSION=snapshot
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-current.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-current
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.linuxprinting.org/download/foomatic/${SOURCE}
        WEB_SITE=http://www.linuxprinting.org/foomatic.html
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
   SOURCE_IGNORE=unversioned
         ENTERED=20020405
        KEYWORDS="printer xml"
           SHORT="Foomatic printing system's XML data generators for HP's HPIJS driver."
cat << EOF

Foomatic is a database-driven system for integrating free software printer
drivers with common spoolers under Unix.  It supports CUPS, LPRng, LPD, GNUlpr,
PPR, PDQ, CPS, and direct spooler-less printing with every free software
printer driver known to us and every printer known to work with these drivers.

This part contains the Foomatic XML data generators for HP's HPIJS driver.

For updated PPDs, go to the folloinwg URL:
http://www.linuxprinting.org/printer_list.cgi

EOF
